gw.pl.persistence.core

Class Key

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.pl.persistence.core.Key
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Key>

    public class Key
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Key>
    Represents the primary key value for a KeyableBean. The key is a pair consisting of the root entity type and the integral (long) value.

      • getType

        public IEntityType getType()
        Gets the more specific entity type associated with this key, if available. If unavailable, then this will return the root type.

        NOTE: Generally, when a subtype bean is retrieved from the database, its Key value will contain the subtype entity type. However, there is no guarantee that the subtype will be set correctly for a given key, so use of this method for anything other than display is discouraged.

      • isTemporary

        public boolean isTemporary()
        Determines whether the key is "temporary", which means it is a negative long minted by the bundle to which the entity was added for insert.

        NOTE: This method is not a reliable way of determining whether a bean is "new" or being inserted. The reason is that there is a window, albeit a small one, where permanent IDs are assigned to "new" beans. This happens just prior to message generation during commit. Instead, to determine whether a bean is "new," use the KeyableBean.isNew() method.
